replies.body:
{{champion:86}}: "DEMACIA!!"
{{champion:86}} **Shut down** {{champion:412}} 
You {{champion:67}}: Just as planned..

I main ADC and the best thing is when the supp accidentally KS's and start apologising, about to completely break down and expects you to totally lambaste them for it 

{{item:3070}} {{champion:89}} {{item:3070}} 


'It's OK man, well played' {{champion:67}}

The truth is most of the benefit of the kill comes from farming unhindered, their loss of farm, taking drake and pushing turrets rather than the kill itself; often supps seem to accidentally KS, whilst saving me from a really close fight with the enemy ADC (when they pop their CC or something) so I am happy.

I had an ADC get angry at me for taking a kill. I Took it because i knew that my ADC wouldn't be able to tower dive for the last hit having like 10% hp and all..
Then later a 1 hit kill got away because i knew my adc would get angry at me for finishing him off, but my adc died tower diving him. He got angry at me because it was somehow my fault the kill got away(i could have flash Q'd him under turret but i refrained), while only he died..my W was on CD at the time as well.

{{champion:37}}
